 Add Controller_Joystick * Level 2.2 Add Gear 3 (90%?)</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="(,,%mT0(SgRRqdyw`czw"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="+szbCBBm?|lNtknuBf0k"><field name="TEXT">Basic Comment_Colors Usage:: Black: Very Big Picture, Blue: Big Picture, Green: Following Block_Code Moddable, Orange: Question/TODO, Magenta: Special Multi-Purpose </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Tn/QCw+lPJ}$-~^:1QEE"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="oQ/}IiUHi=OMm|OJIu*i"><field name="TEXT">micro:bit Ver2 Warning during Download is Ignorable Yet Courteously Helpful</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="=LuK=)PyW;B4;1cV]Hy]"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="9H:hL5Mcv3iq1e!q4`(R"><field name="TEXT">'if_then' mini-stacks useful for modular 3-D code select/duplicate/move/delete</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="8}f*Q8h0:#@[2Dk.elX="><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="L?kNFMjjS2.;B-igClL?"><field name="TEXT">Light_Gray Functions non-editable (backend staff-use code only)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="hrOT~G0J$n-HR=?z?Lw8"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="C9#503h4G|hb:53-ZH3_"><field name="TEXT">For Group_CHannel_# (Bot_Id): Propose: 1-10 Staff Use, 11-99 Student Use</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="|k!9Q.-HWf5*{T#4.nTC"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="=5Z^p3Ct:pf8]3@v{Gpw"><field name="TEXT">SW Reset: Long_Press Logo for 3 sec min</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="F%5B6YE^_FRd#BQs|wf@"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="glm[W?F%0R[`d,W/fNww"><field name="TEXT">Built-in Diagnostic Test: Short_Press Logo for 1 sec max</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="bw0r:pUrOnT)f+,*_4x?"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="W5@RCuR+AD|%2p!s/S5e"><field name="TEXT">'Blocks' Window homes 'on start'_stack as top_left corner of editor_screen, until 'on start' is moved below, then next stack to right presides</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="Tb?jATAq0(/l11b;Lwm$"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="|K_M1!wd1Q8soQaZZ#)b"><field name="TEXT">All These Levels are Intermediate Level Coding due to Networking Pairing Involved.  Basic Diagnostic Servo_Motors (Autonomoous) is Beginner Level.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="e5Xsg`lupfx]Yo,HInK)"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="ghK3|e,=.iN])u#PbTfV"><field name="TEXT">This Intermediate Level Network_Pairing has 1sec_Lag Response Time; The Other Advanced Level Network_Pairing has Real_Time Response Time.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="|49o[_EkAV?pVrhAoEpy"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="ZzHuNG6(K@P+2R(j0kg_"><field name="TEXT">For Level 1, can keep 'Forward: set manual_servo_motors' Block functional, yet reset to 0 all other 'set manual_servo_motors' Blocks for Discovery Learning</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="g]:-~`F5R+PJIa/I0B1O"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="Se]a@Ct+%ynwu41^cqtj"><field name="TEXT">If duplicate stacks exist, then the highest stack is active and others are non_active</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="controls_if" id="DX)z@R`g/5vW9eNr}^-d"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="^g`]_!:h[}rZ^lO-u!@#"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id=",K]l+?`R(Ki2oR+ueqi("><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="`)L9qwGa4n;-Nk*Td/@B"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="s`=FD,*3_7ch].~|VB|,"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="trl8,3HCM=B.~-XY1;QY"><field name="TEXT">Upon open file, Editor zooms in on closest stack to right of original_origin from project_creation</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="y^Y5Ey+6bUUN}.)8tH0O"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="XwDUpV50e;D-v{_j`5]|"><field name="TEXT">Semantic Naming prefers '_' vs. '-' since latter can be conufused with minus_sign</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="FFkn5fV8ZxeSE_r~Q%~7"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id=";yjnjT_SI#U+gMTPNW1g"><field name="TEXT">'every 360000 ms' (1 hour) Stacks can be ignored, esp w/ 'if false' embedded</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="HT6g2#P65Mx5F|wXf9M#"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="Ixe)8-^n?hz25ydj}TGc"><field name="TEXT">Avoid using 'show leds' Block since will cause lag &amp; degrade real-time response</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="l4xt~1oD^]OCOe_K]N(d"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="M_.S1H:~@$G%oVgswrQ1"><field name="TEXT">Seems like 'signficant' changes to JavaScript can activate 'format code', rearrange stacks to original position</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="cPI4(}2n^k`a9FP2=m?Y"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="n)I.KN+_gIRm1i%i.#z9"><field name="TEXT">Important 'system' variables are 1) _system_Hw_DeviceType__* (Hw=Hardware) and 2) _system_Sw_ModeState__* (Sw=Software)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="!Zdr/hyS1Y*i8%tRaIUk"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="MnD.GJn3?7{y=PKQW~F1"><field name="TEXT">If Buttons C-F for Gears/Misc, Maybe 'Logo Up/Down' for 'Servo_Arm Up/Down'</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="#!cr$3j$6#{?MYW8)Q}*"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="_sH=,j*Z|Q=35Eq(UHMF"><field name="TEXT">'Rotatedisplay' could be used on Bot's Led_Screen, but causes light flickering on bottom row, so maybe avoid</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="hC~hdKI(Ax.oNe%88#Zn"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="{b[9j[6@62.g3+1RW(uX"><field name="TEXT">Reliable/Faster Response If Screen_Led_Graphics After Important Action Blocks Above</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="6JLDHkTb=7Jm((`_fs;s"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="p]%yR7OK*^4i^pmR6gf_"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="{Au^Cu(MLROhJ;M[ZDU{"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="Fc},uyKs@@M5e0a[Hj;%"><field name="TEXT">Main upgrade from Lv1 to Lv2 is replacing cpu_laggy 'show leds' block with cpu_fast 'plox x _ y _' block, such as below: </field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="F73W^^/SS#56e*/sjYk_"><mutation elseif="4" else="1"></mutation><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="DXHBO},A17sR{lGMJ,+l"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></sh